HEADWORD: Observation car
<hw>Ob`ser*va"tion car</hw>. <def>A railway passenger car made so as to
facilitate seeing the scenery en route; a car open, or with glass sides,
or with a kind of open balcony at the rear.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

